\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. H. pyrenaicum} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 596 (1753). Rhizome usually horizontal, bearing erect, unbranched, pubescent flowering stems up to 45 cm. Leaves 3-7 × 2-5 cm, mostly basal, ovate to ovate-orbicular or elliptical, obtuse, crenate, ciliate, long-petiolate. Bracts 4-11 mm, ovate-acute or -acuminate, entire, membranous, ciliate. Corolla 17-21 mm, dark bluish-violet, twice as long as calyx. 2n = 12.{\i  Grassy places in mountains; calcicole. Pyrenees,} Alps. Au Ga Ge He Hs It Ju.
